card.name: Project Proposal
card.desc:
Project Name: Art Gallery
-------

Project Summary: 
------
Creating a reusable site for visual artists to cleanly display work, allow for customer contact/commission requesting, and list upcoming events. This site will allow for the client to be able to upload and change images and data easily- and will include a simple dashboard form to do this. 

Teammates:
--------
- Akop
- Andy
- Ashley
- Brant

Tech Stack:
-------
- CSS Framework: Materialize
- Templating engine: Handlebars
- New Technology: Watermark NPM & Materialize


User Stories: 
--------
Artist:

- Clean, uncluttered display of artwork
- All profits (or most) go to artist
- Upcoming events/locations

Viewer:

- Explore custom artwork
- Learn about the artist
- Upcoming events/locations

Who's doing What:
-------
- Front End: Ashley & Andy
- Back End: Akop & Brant

listing.overview: Attach branches, commits, issues, and pull requests to cards, and at a glance see the status of pull requests on your boards.
listing.description:
The GitHub Power-Up for Trello let’s teams track everything that’s going on in GitHub directly from their Trello boards.  Bring perspective to your codebase by attaching pull requests, issues, branches, and more directly to their respective cards.  In a glance, see whether a PR has been merged, the status of checks, who’s assigned to a PR, and more. Checks will also display as visual badges on the front of cards color coded to their status.

- Attach branches, commits, issues and pull requests directly to cards.
- See the status of pull requests on the front of cards.
- Identify cards that have not passed their checks with color coded badges that display on the front of cards.
- Developers and managers can easily jump into GitHub to work on assigned tasks in a single click.
- Associate one or more GitHub repositories with a board.
- The GitHub Power-Up supports both GitHub and GitHub Enterprise instances.

![screenshot](https://github.trello.services/images/screenshots/GitHub_1.jpg)
![screenshot](https://github.trello.services/images/screenshots/GitHub_2.jpg)
![screenshot](https://github.trello.services/images/screenshots/GitHub_3.jpg)

card.desc:

- git checkout master

Step 2 Pull master branch:

- git pull

- New branch:
 - git checkout -b ${branch name}
- Existing branch:

 - git checkout ${branch name}

Step 4 Work in your branch
Step 5 Push your branch:

- git push origin {branch name}

card.name: Git Pull Requests
card.desc:
Step 1 Go to github, put in pull request:

- Click on Pull Request
- Click on New Pull Request
- Add needed comments (You can view your code at the bottom)
- Click Create Pull Request

Step 2 Approve Pull Request:

- Click Pull Requests
- Click on the Request you want
- Click Add your Review
- Check Code, comment and approve as needed
- Submit Review
- Merge Pull Request
- Confirm Merge
- Delete the branch if it is unneeded

cards.desc:
Project Name: Art Gallery
-------

Project Summary: 
------
Creating a reusable site for visual artists to cleanly display work, allow for customer contact/commission requesting, and list upcoming events. This site will allow for the client to be able to upload and change images and data easily- and will include a simple dashboard form to do this. 

Teammates:
--------
- Akop
- Andy
- Ashley
- Brant

Tech Stack:
-------
- CSS Framework: Materialize
- Templating engine: Handlebars
- New Technology: Watermark NPM & Materialize


User Stories: 
--------
Artist:

- Clean, uncluttered display of artwork
- All profits (or most) go to artist
- Upcoming events/locations

Viewer:

- Explore custom artwork
- Learn about the artist
- Upcoming events/locations

Who's doing What:
-------
- Front End: Ashley & Andy
- Back End: Akop & Brant
